AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 6001* House Bill No. 6004
by deleting all language after the caption and substituting:
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1.
(a) This act is known and may be cited as the "Education Freedom Act of 2025."
(b) The Tennessee advisory commission on intergovernmental relations (TACIR)
shall conduct a study to determine the state's fiscal implications that the "Education
Freedom Scholarship Act" proposed in the original filed version of House Bill 6004 /
Senate Bill 6001 of the 1st Extraordinary Session of the 114th General Assembly would
generate for the first ten (10) years following passage of such proposed version. TACIR
shall report its findings to the general assembly by January 1, 2026.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect July 1, 2025, the public welfare requiring it.
